sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K299802
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Aactag - like a biobrick scar but first T changed to A
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This is a virtual part useful to anyone working with Anderson's RBS library.
First nucleotide of the biobrick suffix is varies in the library, some RBSes have T, wchich results in a regular suffix, but other hace c,G or A. This Modified scar is to help in sillico assembly of the constructs that use Anderson's RBSes.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anna Olchowik

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K299107
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: T.xbaI.G (T followed by xbaI site and additional G to behave like biobrick prefix after xbaI digest)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is just to obtain accurate sequences while working with Anderson's RBS library in original vector.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anna Olchowik

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: mRFP derivative. Ex548nm/Em562. yeast codon optimized.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: ryu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Contains N- and C-terminal linker sequences (with homology to biobrick parts BBa_E2060 (mCherry), BBa_E2020 (Cerulean CFP), and BBa_E2030 (Venus YFP) to facilitate color swapping in yeast. Adds N-"MATSG" and "GSGTA"-C. to published amino acid sequence. Double TAATAA stop codon. Missing EcoRI, HindIII, NotI, NdeI, XhoI, RsrII, BamHI, NcoI, BglI, SpeI, XbaI, and PstI. except for 5' and 3' ends no significant sequence identity runs to mCherry (BBa_E2060).
